claudeqt for Debian/Ubuntu
==========================

WHAT THIS PACKAGE IS
--------------------
ClaudeQt is a native Qt6 desktop GUI for the Claude Code CLI. It provides
a project/session tree, tabbed code editor with syntax highlighting, chat
shell, multi-window support, and crash-safe persistence. ClaudeQt never
executes shell commands itself — all AI interaction is delegated to the
Claude Code CLI.

CLAUDE CODE CLI DEPENDENCY
--------------------------
ClaudeQt requires the Claude Code CLI to be installed for AI interaction.
The GUI shell works without it (you can manage projects, sessions, files,
and settings), but submitting chat messages requires a working CLI.

Anthropic does not ship a Debian package for the CLI. It is distributed
via npm and requires Node.js.

INSTALLING THE CLAUDE CODE CLI
------------------------------
1. Check whether Node.js is installed:

       node --version

   If not installed, use the NodeSource PPA or your preferred method:

       curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_lts.x | sudo -E bash -
       sudo apt install nodejs

2. Install the Claude Code CLI globally:

       sudo npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code

3. Verify the installation:

       claude --version

   ClaudeQt requires Claude Code CLI version 2.1.97 or later.

4. Authenticate:

       claude auth login

   Follow the browser-based OAuth flow to link your Anthropic account.

VERIFYING CLI DETECTION
-----------------------
ClaudeQt searches for the 'claude' binary using the standard PATH lookup.
If it is installed to a non-standard location, ensure that location is in
your PATH before launching ClaudeQt.

To verify ClaudeQt can find the CLI:

    which claude && claude --version

Both commands should succeed and the version should be >= 2.1.97.

DATA STORAGE
------------
ClaudeQt stores all session data (projects, sessions, messages, file
buffers, settings) in a SQLite database under:

    $XDG_DATA_HOME/claudeqt/

which defaults to ~/.local/share/claudeqt/ on most systems. The database
uses WAL (Write-Ahead Logging) mode for crash safety.

MULTI-WINDOW SUPPORT
--------------------
Multiple ClaudeQt windows can run simultaneously. A leader-elected IPC hub
over Unix domain sockets coordinates cross-instance notifications so that
changes in one window (new sessions, renamed projects, settings changes)
appear in all windows automatically.

See also:
  /usr/share/doc/claudeqt/copyright
  https://github.com/ayourk/claudeqt (upstream)
